organizations: Collier County Athletes Compete in Aquatics State Games
title: Special Olympics Florida – Collier County
text:
Special Olympics Florida – Collier County Athletes Compete in Aquatics State Games in Sebastian SOFL-Collier 4:13 PM, Oct 7, 2015 4:13 PM, Oct 7, 2015 
A delegation of 6 Special Olympics Florida – Collier County athletes participated in the 2015 State Aquatics Competition in Sebastian, FL on October 3rd and 4th, competing against athletes from around the state. Competition results for Collier athletes are: 
• Adam Rosman: 200M Individual Medley – Silver Medal & 50M Butterfly – Silver Medal 
• Jennifer Socia: 100M Freestyle – Silver Medal & 100M Individual Medley – Gold Medal 
• Brian Francis: 100M Freestyle – Silver Medal & 50M Backstroke – Silver Medal 
• Michael Tulipano: 25M Freestyle – Gold Medal & 25M Backstroke – Silver Medal 
• Martin Grasser: 25M Freestyle – 8th place & 25M Backstroke – Gold Medal 
• Alex Perez: 25M Freestyle – Participant & 25M Backstroke – Participant 
Congratulations to all Collier swimmers on a successful aquatics season, and many thanks to our volunteer coaches who gave so much of their time to train our athletes. 
Special Olympics Florida – Collier County’s programs are possible because of the dedication of hundreds of volunteers who organize, coach, publicize, raise funds, and administer the organization. All financial support for Special Olympics Florida – Collier County comes from local businesses, organizations, and individuals. 
To become a volunteer coach for any sport or to sign up to participate as an athlete or a Unified Partner, please call Special Olympics Florida – Collier County at 239-775-1991, email info@specialolympicscollier.org, or go to www.specialolympicscollier.org.
